http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Cultural-events-for-Republic-Day/article13998358.ece

Deputy Commissioner Srirangaiah has instructed officials to make necessary preparations for Republic Day celebrations on January 26.Speaking at a meeting of district-level officers here on Tuesday, he said that Minister for Social Welfare and district in-charge H. Anjaneya would unfurl the national flag at 9 a.m. and receive the guard of honour. School and college students would gather at the grounds by 8.30 a.m. They would present cultural programmes at SJM auditorium.Mr. Srirangaiah said that the city municipal council would make arrangements for the function and the municipal commissioner would supervise the arrangements, he added.